org.apache.arrow.vector.ipc

Class WriteChannel

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.arrow.vector.ipc.WriteChannel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable

    public class WriteChannel
extends Object
implements AutoCloseable
    Wrapper around a WritableByteChannel that maintains the position as well adding some common serialization utilities. All write methods in this class follow full write semantics, i.e., write calls only return after requested data has been fully written. Note this is different from java WritableByteChannel interface where partial write is allowed
